Table 4 gives the goodness of fit tests of the interarrival time distribution for Port C, and the following hypotheses can be established: H0: The data are fitted by a “Gamma” distribution. H1: The data does not fit a “Gamma” distribution.
The significance level for the goodness of fit test was α = 0.05. The null hypothesis cannot be rejected since the p-values for both K-S and A-D goodness of fit tests were > α. The StatFit program lists the appropriate distributions according to their relative goodness of fit, i.e. fitness percentage. The distributions that are appropriate for the interarrival times are listed in Table 4 according to the fitness percentages.

